                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.20235/405a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-14T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 14, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>274. The Attorney General has informed the Department that it would be highly
                    desirable if certain of the spies currently being apprehended by the Argentine
                    authorities could be brought to the United <pb facs="0400" n="386"
                        xml:id="pg_386"/> States for further questioning and possible internment
                    here. Please advise whether in your judgment the Argentine authorities would be
                    disposed to be cooperative in this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
